});
One of the biggest advantages of Promises is .Instead of nesting functions like callbacks, you can just return values in a  block and pass it along the chain.fetchUser(1)
  .then(user => fetchPosts(user.id))
  .then(posts => fetchComments(posts[0].id))
  .then(comments => {
    console.log('Comments:', comments);
  });
